data.description: Charming early 1900's home with 5 acres m/l.  This remodeled home offers one bedroom and one bath, living room, and kitchen, all on main level, containing approx 938 sq ft, with additional square footage upstairs that could easily be completed for additional living space.  New electrical, plumbing, floors, insulation and walls, hvac, roof, windows and doors...over the last few years, this home has been completely remodeled.  The home offers cozy covered porches, wood burning stove in the living room, nice yard with mature trees, outbuilding and acreage! The property also offers a detached RV carport with 30 amp service and detached garage. If you are looking for a second home, starter home or possibly downsizing, check out this property! Conveniently located to both Jamestown and Byrdstown TN, Big South Fork National Park, Pickett State Park, & Dale Hollow Lake! The property lies along State Hwy 127 and is centrally located to Knoxville and Nashville. *Active Contingency Still Showing*
